  "title": "Senior R&D Electronics Design Engineer (Woodlands - Life Sciences)",
  "description": "<p>Our client is a leading American life sciences company with more than 8,000 employees globally. Having been in Singapore for close to 20 years, the company has a new headcount now for the R&D EE team.</p><p><strong>Senior R&D Electronics Design Engineer</strong><br /><br /><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p><p>·       You will be part of a team of R&D Engineers here in Singapore working on design and development of company’s products. </p><p>·       You will be involved in each stage of the product development life cycle including requirement analysis, analysing user needs, coming up with design specifications and design implementation.  </p><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><p>·       Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Electrical / Electronics Engineering with more than 5 years of experience in EE design and development. </p><p>·       Experience with working on at least 1-2 product development projects.</p><p>·       Strong knowledge in analog, digital, and mixed signal circuit design</p><p>Interested applicants, kindly send in a copy of your updated resume in WORD document to <u><strong>hr@searchstaffing.com.sg</strong></u> stating your current and expected remuneration together with notice period required to current employer.</p><p>You can also contact Vincent Low for a confidential discussion at 6749 4236.</p><p>EA Personnel Registration No: R1324700</p>",
